1
00:00:14,473 --> 00:00:16,266
(HIGH PITCHED BUZZING)

2
00:00:19,228 --> 00:00:21,688
-Have you got everything?
-I've got everything. Don't worry.

3
00:00:21,772 --> 00:00:23,190
Be careful.

4
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:25,567
-You have to call Mo about...
-Never mind Mo.

5
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:34,368
-Okay, I'm going now. I love you.
-Love you.

6
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,500
-Love you.
-Bye.

7
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:08,694
-So where are we going?
-Further than we've ever gone before.

8
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:14,575
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

9
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:57,242
It's the year five billion and twenty-three.

10
00:01:57,367 --> 00:02:02,372
We're in the galaxy M87 and this...
This is New Earth.

11
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:04,958
ROSE: It's just...

12
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:09,630
That's just...

13
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:13,008
Not bad. Not bad at all.

14
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,885
ROSE: That's amazing.

15
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:18,013
I'll never get used to this, never.

16
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:21,767
Different ground beneath my feet.
Different sky.

17
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:24,102
What's that smell?

18
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:28,857
-Apple grass.
-Apple grass. It's beautiful.

19
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,444
Oh, I love this.

20
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:37,449
Can I just say, travelling with you...
I love it.

21
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,576
Me, too.

22
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:41,244
Come on.

23
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:47,417
Human! She's pure-blood human.

24
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,713
Closer, closer.

25
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:03,892
So, the year five billion,
the sun expands, the Earth gets roasted.

26
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,560
That was our first date.

27
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,312
We had chips.

28
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,899
So anyway, planet gone, all rocks and dust,

29
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:13,527
but the human race lives on,
spread out across the stars.

30
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:16,530
As soon as the Earth burns up,
oh, they get all nostalgic.

31
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:20,117
Big revival movement. They find this place.

32
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:23,453
Same size as the Earth,
same air, same orbit, lovely.

33
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:25,414
The call goes out, the humans move in.

34
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:27,708
-What's the city called?
-New New York.

35
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:29,584
-Oh, come on.
-It is!

36
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:32,129
It's the City of New New York.

37
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,507
Strictly speaking, it's the fifteenth
New York since the original.

38
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:36,842
So that makes it

39
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:40,345
New New New New New New New New New
New New New New New New York.

40
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,391
-What?
-You're so different.

41
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:46,226
New new Doctor.

42
00:03:48,979 --> 00:03:51,690
CASSANDRA: Impossible!
I recognise that child.

43
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,859
Her face! Show me her face!

44
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:55,318
Closer, closer.

45
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:58,530
Face, face, face!

46
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:03,744
Can we go and visit New New York?
So good they named it twice.

47
00:04:03,827 --> 00:04:07,831
Well, I thought we might go there first.

48
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:10,917
-Why? What is it?
-Some sort of hospital.

49
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:14,004
Green moon on the side,
that's the universal symbol for hospitals.

50
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:17,966
I got this. A message on the psychic paper.

51
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:20,343
Someone wants to see me.

52
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:23,597
Oh, and I thought we were just sightseeing.

53
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,307
Come on, then,
let's go and buy some grapes.

54
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:30,896
Rose Tyler! I knew it!

55
00:04:31,188 --> 00:04:34,191
-That dirty blonde assassin.
-She's coming here, mistress.

56
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:37,527
But this is beyond coincidence.
This is destiny.

57
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:40,155
At last, I can be revenged on that little...

58
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,823
A bit rich coming from you.

59
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:44,242
I can't help it. I don't like hospitals.
They give me the creeps.

60
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:46,745
(PA) The pleasure gardens
will now take visitors

61
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:51,041
carrying green or blue identification cards
for the next 15 minutes.

62
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:55,712
Visitors are reminded that cuttings
from the gardens are not permitted.

63
00:04:55,796 --> 00:04:59,049
Very smart. Not exactly NHS.

64
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:00,967
No shop. I like the little shop.

65
00:05:01,051 --> 00:05:03,637
I thought this far in the future,
they'd have cured everything.

66
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:08,350
The human race moves on,
but so do the viruses. It's an ongoing war.

67
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:11,311
(PA) Hope, harmony and health.

68
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:15,607
-They're cats.
-Now, don't stare.

69
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:19,402
Think what you look like to them.
All pink and yellow.

70
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,364
That's where I'd put the shop, right there.

71
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:26,409
Ward 26, thanks.

72
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:28,537
Override controls.

73
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,247
Hold on, hold on!

74
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,458
-Oh, too late. I'm going up.
-All right, there's another lift.

75
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:34,751
Ward 26!

76
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:37,420
-And watch out for the disinfectant.
-Watch out for what?

77
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:39,422
-The disinfectant!
-The what?

78
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:41,758
The dis... Oh, you'll find out.

79
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:51,268
Ward 26, thanks.

80
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:00,026
(PA) Commence stage one disinfection.

81
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:06,533
Commence stage one disinfection.

82
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:42,152
The human child is clean.

83
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:45,030
Erm, I'm looking for ward 26.

84
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:46,865
This way, Rose Tyler.

85
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:05,884
Nice place.

86
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:09,512
No shop downstairs. I'd have a shop.
Not a big one, just a shop.

87
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:11,139
So people can shop.

88
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,516
The hospital is a place of healing.

89
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:17,854
A shop does some people
the world of good. Not me, other people.

90
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:24,945
The Sisters of Plenitude
take a lifelong vow to help and to mend.

91
00:07:25,028 --> 00:07:26,488
(GROANING)

92
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,281
Excuse me!

93
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:32,744
Members of the public may only gaze
upon the Duke of Manhattan

94
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:35,288
with written permission from
the Senate of New New York.

95
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:38,875
-That's petrifold regression, right?
-I'm dying, sir.

96
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:43,755
A lifetime of charity and abstinence
and it ends like this.

97
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,715
Any statements made by
the Duke of Manhattan

98
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,051
may not be made public
without official clearance.

99
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,220
Frau Clovis...

100
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:53,807
I'm so weak.

101
00:07:53,932 --> 00:07:56,434
Sister Jatt, a little privacy, please.

102
00:07:59,354 --> 00:08:01,648
-He'll be up and about in no time.
-I doubt it.

103
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:05,902
Petrifold regression, he's turning to stone.
There won't be a cure for a thousand years.

104
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,821
He might be up and about
but only as a statue.

105
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:10,281
Have faith in the Sisterhood.

106
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:12,283
But is there no one here you recognise?

107
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:15,996
It's rather unusual to visit
without knowing the patient.

108
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:18,623
No, I think I've found him.

109
00:08:21,751 --> 00:08:24,963
Novice Hame, if I can leave
this gentleman in your care.

110
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:28,800
Oh, I think my friend got lost.
Rose Tyler. Could you ask at reception?

111
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,510
Certainly, sir.

112
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:36,725
I'm afraid the Face of Boe is asleep.
That's all he tends to do these days.

113
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,144
Are you a friend, or...

114
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:43,148
We met just the once. On Platform One.
What's wrong with him?

115
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:45,942
I'm so sorry. I thought you knew.

116
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:49,070
The Face of Boe is dying.

117
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:54,284
-Of what?
-Old age. One thing we can't cure.

118
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:59,372
He's thousands of years old,
some people say millions,

119
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:01,458
although that's impossible.

120
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:04,377
Oh, I don't know. I like impossible.

121
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:10,216
I'm here. I look a bit different, but it's me.

122
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,469
It's the Doctor.

123
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:20,185
(THE FACE OF BOE GROANING)

124
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,952
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

125
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:42,207
MAN: Look at me!

126
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:44,626
Isn't it wonderful?

127
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:49,380
Well, you never know what
your life is going to be like, ever.

128
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:51,633
I'm bored with this drink. Anyway...

129
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:56,387
Oh, hello, darling. Oh! Now don't. Stop It.

130
00:09:56,513 --> 00:09:58,139
Wait a minute. That's...

131
00:09:58,223 --> 00:09:59,390
Peek-a-boo!

132
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:01,518
Don't you come
anywhere near me, Cassandra.

133
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,687
Why? What do you think I'm going to do?
Flap you to death?

134
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:08,900
-Yeah, but what about Gollum?
-Oh, that's just Chip. He's my pet.

135
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,443
I worship the mistress.

136
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:13,113
Moisturise me, moisturise me.

137
00:10:14,197 --> 00:10:17,951
He's not even a proper life form.
He's a force-grown clone.

138
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:20,662
I model led him on my favourite pattern.

139
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:22,789
But he's so faithful.

140
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,874
Chip sees to my physical needs.

141
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:28,586
I hope that means food.
How come you're still alive?

142
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:31,714
-After you murdered me?
-That was your own fault.

143
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:34,217
The brain of my mistress survived.

144
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:37,804
And her pretty blue eyes
were salvaged from the bin.

145
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:39,514
What about the skin?

146
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:43,143
I saw it. You got ripped apart.

147
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:46,229
That piece of skin
was taken from the front of my body.

148
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:47,939
This piece is the back.

149
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:51,067
-Right, so you're talking out of your...
-Ask not!

150
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:55,738
The mistress was lucky to survive.
Chip secreted m'lady into the hospital.

151
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:58,283
-So they don't know you're here?
-Chip steals medicine.

152
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:01,703
Helps m'lady. Soothes her.

153
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:04,164
-Strokes her.
-You can stop right there, Chip.

154
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:07,750
But I'm so alone, hidden down here.

155
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:11,254
-The last human in existence.
-Don't start that again.

156
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:14,048
-They've called this planet New Earth.
-A vegetable patch.

157
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:17,760
And there's millions of humans out there,
millions of them.

158
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:19,262
Mutant stock.

159
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:23,224
They evolved, Cassandra, they just evolved.
Like they should.

160
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:27,520
You stayed still, you got yourself
all pickled and preserved,

161
00:11:27,604 --> 00:11:29,314
and what good did it do you?

162
00:11:29,439 --> 00:11:33,651
I remember that night.
Drinks for the Ambassador of Thrace.

163
00:11:34,444 --> 00:11:37,822
That was the last time anyone told me
I was beautiful.

164
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:41,659
After that, it all became such hard work.

165
00:11:41,743 --> 00:11:43,912
You've got a knack for survival,
I'll give you that.

166
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:48,416
But I've not been idle, Rose.
Tucked away, underneath this hospital,

167
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:52,337
I've been listening.
The Sisters are hiding something.

168
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,088
What do you mean?

169
00:11:54,172 --> 00:11:56,591
These cats have secrets.

170
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:59,802
Hush. Let me whisper, come close.

171
00:12:00,178 --> 00:12:04,265
You must be joking
if you think I'm coming anywhere near you.

172
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:06,476
Chip! Activate the psycho-graft!

173
00:12:06,601 --> 00:12:09,479
I can't move. Cassandra, let me go!

174
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:14,025
-What are you doing?
-The lady's moving on.

175
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:17,987
It's goodbye trampoline and hello blondie!

176
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:32,669
Mistress.

177
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:35,255
Moisturise me.

178
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,180
How bizarre. Arms.

179
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:47,267
Fingers!

180
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:49,227
Hair!

181
00:12:49,936 --> 00:12:52,021
Let me see, let me see.

182
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:55,858
Oh, my God!

183
00:12:55,942 --> 00:12:58,027
I'm a chav.

184
00:12:59,153 --> 00:13:01,447
(PA) Hope, harmony and health.

185
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:04,575
Hope, harmony and health.

186
00:13:04,701 --> 00:13:07,370
That's very kind. There's no need.

187
00:13:07,954 --> 00:13:10,623
-You're the one working.
-There's not much to do.

188
00:13:10,707 --> 00:13:13,084
Just maintain his smoke.

189
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:17,255
And I suppose I'm company.
I can hear him singing sometimes,

190
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,799
in my mind.

191
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,760
Such ancient songs.

192
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:24,637
Am I the only visitor?

193
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:27,807
The rest of Boekind
became extinct long ago.

194
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,601
He's the only one left.

195
00:13:30,727 --> 00:13:35,148
Legend says that the Face of Boe
has watched the universe grow old.

196
00:13:35,732 --> 00:13:38,276
There's all sorts of superstitions
around him.

197
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:42,905
One story says that just before his death,

198
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:45,908
the Face of Boe will impart his great secret.

199
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:50,371
That he will speak those words
only to one like himself.

200
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:53,291
-What does that mean?
-It's just a story.

201
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:55,251
Tell me the rest.

202
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:59,714
It's said he'll talk to a wanderer.
To the man without a home.

203
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,425
The lonely god.

204
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:11,267
Look at me. From class to brass.

205
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:13,978
Although...

206
00:14:14,479 --> 00:14:15,730
Ooh.

207
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:19,567
Curves. Oh, baby!

208
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,986
It's like living inside a bouncy castle.

209
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,822
-The mistress is beautiful.
-Absolument.

210
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,700
Oh, but look.

211
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:31,329
Aw, the brain meat expired.

212
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:34,415
My old mistress has gone.

213
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:37,293
But safe and sound in here.

214
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,046
But what of the Rose child's mind?

215
00:14:41,172 --> 00:14:44,634
Tucked away. I can just about access
the surface memory. She's...

216
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:50,848
God, she's with the Doctor.

217
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,478
That man, he's the Doctor.

218
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:58,981
The same Doctor with a new face!

219
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:01,150
That hypocrite!

220
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:04,278
I must get the name of his surgeon.

221
00:15:04,362 --> 00:15:08,491
I could do with a little work. Although...

222
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:12,078
nice rear bumper.

223
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:15,081
(PHONE RINGING)

224
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:19,043
Oh! It seems to be ringing.
Is it meant to ring?

225
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,170
A primitive communications device.

226
00:15:21,254 --> 00:15:23,089
DOCTOR: Rose, where are you?

227
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:26,092
-How does she speak?
-Old Earth cockney.

228
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:27,385
Um...

229
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:30,304
-Wotcha.
-Where've you been?

230
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:34,016
-How long does it take to get to ward 267
-I'm on my way, guv'nor.

231
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:37,728
I shall proceed up the apples and pears.

232
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:41,732
You'll never guess!
I'm with the Face of Boe. Remember him?

233
00:15:42,859 --> 00:15:45,194
Of course I do.

234
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:48,448
That big old...boat race.

235
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:50,533
I'd better go. See you in a minute.

236
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:53,536
(CHUCKLING)
I didn't think I was going to make it.

237
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:57,874
It's that man again!
He's my good luck charm.

238
00:15:57,999 --> 00:16:00,585
Come in! Don't be shy.

239
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:03,963
Any friendship expressed by
the Duke of Manhattan does not constitute

240
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:06,841
-a form of legal contract.
-Winch me up!

241
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:13,556
-Up! Look at me. No sign of infection.
-Champagne, sir?

242
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,558
No, thanks.

243
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:19,520
-You had petrifold regression, right?
-"Had" being the operative word.

244
00:16:19,604 --> 00:16:21,063
Past tense!

245
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:23,357
Completely cured.

246
00:16:23,441 --> 00:16:27,487
-But that's impossible.
-Primitive species would accuse us of magic

247
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:31,032
but it's merely
the tender application of science.

248
00:16:31,574 --> 00:16:33,075
How on earth did you cure him?

249
00:16:33,201 --> 00:16:35,411
How on New Earth, you might say.

250
00:16:35,536 --> 00:16:38,206
-What's in that solution?
-A simple remedy.

251
00:16:38,289 --> 00:16:39,624
Then tell me what it is.

252
00:16:39,749 --> 00:16:43,127
I'm sorry. Patient confidentiality.

253
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:46,631
I don't believe we've met.
My name is Matron Casp.

254
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:47,924
I'm the Doctor.

255
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:50,593
I think you'll find
that we are the doctors here.

256
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:53,095
Matron Casp,
you're needed in intensive care.

257
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:55,223
If you would excuse me.

258
00:16:56,641 --> 00:17:00,311
It's happened again.
One of the patients is conscious.

259
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:02,522
Well, we can't have that.

260
00:17:02,605 --> 00:17:04,524
This Doctor man is dangerous.

261
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:07,276
Dangerous and clever.

262
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:11,030
I might need a mind like his.
The Sisterhood is up to something.

263
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:15,368
Remember that old Earth saying?
"Never trust a nun...

264
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:19,580
"never trust a nurse and never trust a cat."

265
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:20,957
Perfume?

266
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:29,131
It was having a perfectly
normal blood-wash,

267
00:17:29,257 --> 00:17:33,010
then all of a sudden it started crying.
It's this one.

268
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:36,389
CREATURE: Please.

269
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:39,100
-Look at its eyes. So alive.
-Help me.

270
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:41,811
-Positively sparkling.
-Please.

271
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:45,064
-Where am I?
-And speech.

272
00:17:45,147 --> 00:17:47,149
How can it even have a vocabulary?

273
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:50,820
Sister Corvin has written a thesis
on the migration of sentience.

274
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:54,907
She calls it 7he Echo of Life.
It's well worth a read.

275
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:56,534
Help me.

276
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:58,828
I've seen enough, thank you.

277
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:03,749
If this happens again, we might
have to review our brainstem policy.

278
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:07,920
-And what should we do with the patient?
-Standard procedure. Incinerate.

279
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:12,508
(SCREAMING)

280
00:18:14,885 --> 00:18:18,723
(PA) Ambient temperature
stands at 14 degrees cohezic.

281
00:18:18,973 --> 00:18:21,642
Repeat, 14 degrees cohezic.

282
00:18:21,726 --> 00:18:25,771
This temperature is designed to promote
healing and well-being.

283
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:29,025
There you are.
Come and look at this patient.

284
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:32,111
Marconi's disease.
Should take years to recover.

285
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,155
Two days. I've never seen anything like it.

286
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:37,366
They've invented a cell-washing cascade.
It's amazing.

287
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:41,162
Their medical science is way advanced.
And this one.

288
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:45,166
Pallidome pancrosis.
Kills you in ten minutes, and he's fine.

289
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:49,462
I need to find a terminal.
I've got to see how they do this.

290
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:53,549
'Cause if they've got the best medicine
in the world, then why is it such a secret?

291
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:55,885
I can't Adam and Eve it.

292
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:58,929
What... What's with the voice?

293
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:02,558
I don't know, just larking about. New Earth.

294
00:19:03,893 --> 00:19:05,561
New me.

295
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,522
Well, I can talk. New new Doctor.

296
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:11,275
Mmm, aren't you just?

297
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:22,995
(STUTTERING) Terminal's this way.

298
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:30,503
Yeah, still got it.

299
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:35,007
No, nothing odd. Surgery. Post-op.

300
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:36,592
Nanodentistry.

301
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:38,719
No sign of a shop. They should have a shop.

302
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:40,429
No, it's missing something else.

303
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:43,265
When I was downstairs,
those nurse-cat-nuns

304
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:46,519
were talking about intensive care,
but where is it?

305
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,062
You're right. Well done.

306
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:50,940
Why would they hide a whole department?

307
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:54,735
It's got to be there somewhere.
Search the subframe.

308
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,862
What if the subframe's locked?

309
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:58,781
Try the installation protocol.

310
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,033
Yeah. Course. Sorry.

311
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,120
(DOOR OPENING)

312
00:20:13,671 --> 00:20:15,297
Intensive care.

313
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:18,300
Certainly looks intensive.

314
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:04,472
That's disgusting. What's wrong with him?

315
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:07,600
I'm sorry.

316
00:21:09,477 --> 00:21:11,020
I'm so sorry.

317
00:21:27,328 --> 00:21:29,246
What disease is that?

318
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:31,290
All of them.

319
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:35,586
Every single disease in the galaxy.
They've been infected with everything.

320
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:38,088
What about us? Are we safe?

321
00:21:39,173 --> 00:21:41,884
The air's sterile. Just don't touch them.

322
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:52,061
How many patients are there?

323
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:53,979
They're not patients.

324
00:21:54,063 --> 00:21:55,481
But they're sick.

325
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:56,941
They were born sick.

326
00:21:57,066 --> 00:22:00,152
They're meant to be sick.
They exist to be sick.

327
00:22:00,236 --> 00:22:01,570
Lab rats.

328
00:22:01,654 --> 00:22:03,823
No wonder the Sisters
have got a cure for everything.

329
00:22:03,906 --> 00:22:06,033
They've built
the ultimate research laboratory.

330
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:08,077
A human farm!

331
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:10,329
Why don't they just die?

332
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:15,042
Plague carriers. The last to go.

333
00:22:15,251 --> 00:22:17,461
It's for the greater cause.

334
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:20,256
Novice Hame.

335
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:23,133
When you took your vows,
did you agree to this?

336
00:22:23,217 --> 00:22:25,636
The Sisterhood has sworn to help.

337
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:28,681
-What, by killing?
-But they're not real people.

338
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:33,227
They're specially grown.
They have no proper existence.

339
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:35,813
What's the turnover?

340
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:40,442
A thousand a day? Thousand the next?
Thousand the next? How many thousands?

341
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:42,903
For how many years? How many?

342
00:22:42,987 --> 00:22:45,155
Mankind needed us.

343
00:22:45,239 --> 00:22:49,702
They came to this planet
with so many illnesses, we couldn't cope.

344
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,788
We did try. We tried everything.

345
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:56,750
We tried using clone meat and bio-cattle,

346
00:22:56,834 --> 00:22:59,003
but the results were too slow.

347
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:01,797
So the Sisterhood grew its own flesh.

348
00:23:02,673 --> 00:23:05,009
That's all they are. Flesh.

349
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:06,635
These people are alive.

350
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:11,265
But think of those humans
out there, healthy,

351
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,475
and happy, because of us.

352
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:16,729
If they live because of this
then life is worthless.

353
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:20,065
But who are you to decide that?

354
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:21,650
I'm the Doctor.

355
00:23:21,734 --> 00:23:25,696
And if you don't like it, if you want to take
it to a higher authority, there isn't one.

356
00:23:25,779 --> 00:23:27,573
It stops with me.

357
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:30,326
Just to confirm...

358
00:23:30,409 --> 00:23:33,037
none of the humans in the city
actually know about this?

359
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,749
-We thought it best not...
-Hold on. I can understand the bodies,

360
00:23:36,832 --> 00:23:39,960
I can understand your vows,
but one thing I can't understand.

361
00:23:40,044 --> 00:23:43,005
-What have you done to Rose?
-I don't know what you mean.

362
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:44,882
And I'm being very, very calm.

363
00:23:45,007 --> 00:23:46,967
You want to be aware of that.
Very, very calm.

364
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:49,345
And the only reason
I'm being so very, very calm

365
00:23:49,428 --> 00:23:52,014
is that the brain is a delicate thing.

366
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:54,808
Whatever you've done to Rose's head,
I want it reversed.

367
00:23:54,892 --> 00:23:56,644
We haven't done anything.

368
00:23:56,727 --> 00:23:59,104
I'm perfectly fine.

369
00:23:59,188 --> 00:24:02,191
These people are dying
and Rose would care.

370
00:24:04,026 --> 00:24:08,280
All right, clever clogs. Smarty-pants.

371
00:24:10,574 --> 00:24:13,118
-Ladykiller.
-What's happened to you?

372
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:15,621
I knew something
was going on in this hospital

373
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:20,542
but I needed this body
and your mind to find it out.

374
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:22,086
Who are you?

375
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:26,215
The last human.

376
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:27,424
Cassandra?

377
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:29,843
Wake up and smell the perfume.

378
00:24:32,805 --> 00:24:34,056
You've hurt him.

379
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:36,809
I don't understand.
I'll have to fetch Matron.

380
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:38,811
You do that 'cause I want to see her.

381
00:24:38,894 --> 00:24:41,438
Now run along! Sound the alarm!

382
00:24:46,527 --> 00:24:49,530
-Matron, it's that man and the girl.
-We heard the alarm.

383
00:24:49,613 --> 00:24:52,324
Now, get back to work.
Tend to your patients.

384
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:03,002
Let me out! Let me out!

385
00:25:03,085 --> 00:25:07,381
Aren't you lucky there was a spare?
Standing room only.

386
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:09,049
You've stolen Rose's body!

387
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:13,595
Over the years, I've thought of
a thousand ways to kill you, Doctor.

388
00:25:14,555 --> 00:25:17,808
And now that's exactly what I've got.
One thousand diseases.

389
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:20,519
They pump the patients with a top-up
every 10 minutes.

390
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:23,605
You've got about three minutes left.

391
00:25:23,689 --> 00:25:25,107
Enjoy.

392
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:27,651
-Just let Rose go, Cassandra.
-I will.

393
00:25:27,776 --> 00:25:31,780
As soon as I find someone
younger and less common.

394
00:25:31,989 --> 00:25:34,908
Then I'lWl junk her with the waste.
Now hush-a-bye.

395
00:25:34,992 --> 00:25:36,577
It's showtime.

396
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,954
Anything we can do to help?

397
00:25:39,079 --> 00:25:42,124
Straight to the point, whiskers.
I want money.

398
00:25:42,249 --> 00:25:46,795
The Sisterhood is a charity,
we don't give money. We only accept.

399
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:49,631
The humans across the water
pay you a fortune,

400
00:25:49,715 --> 00:25:51,508
and that's exactly what I need.

401
00:25:51,592 --> 00:25:54,470
A one-off payment, that's all I want.

402
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:57,264
Oh, and perhaps a yacht,
in return for which

403
00:25:57,389 --> 00:26:01,393
I will tell the city
nothing of your institutional murder.

404
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:04,813
-Is that a deal?
-I'm afraid not.

405
00:26:04,938 --> 00:26:07,107
I'd really advise you to think about this.

406
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:10,110
Oh, there's no need. I have to decline.

407
00:26:10,194 --> 00:26:13,072
I'll tell them.
And you've no way of stopping me.

408
00:26:13,155 --> 00:26:15,824
You're not exactly nuns with guns.
You're not even armed.

409
00:26:15,908 --> 00:26:19,620
Who needs arms when we have claws?

410
00:26:20,454 --> 00:26:21,872
(SNARLING)

411
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:24,458
Well, nice try. Chip, plan B!

412
00:26:27,336 --> 00:26:29,254
(ALARM SOUNDING)

413
00:26:35,511 --> 00:26:36,929
What have you done?

414
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:39,973
Gave the system a shot of adrenalin,
just to wake them up. See ya!

415
00:26:40,057 --> 00:26:43,060
Don't touch them!
Whatever you do, don't touch!

416
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:46,688
WOMAN: Save us.

417
00:26:48,649 --> 00:26:50,609
I think we should withdraw.

418
00:26:50,692 --> 00:26:53,237
We understood what you did to us.

419
00:26:54,113 --> 00:26:58,367
As part of the machine,
we know the machine.

420
00:26:58,492 --> 00:27:02,287
Fascinating. It's actually
constructing an argument.

421
00:27:02,412 --> 00:27:05,124
And we will end it.

422
00:27:23,976 --> 00:27:26,103
(ALL GROANING) Save us.

423
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:28,856
They're free.

424
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:31,817
By the goddess Santori!

425
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,902
The flesh is free!

426
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:38,407
(GROANING) Stop the pain.

427
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,497
(SCREAMING)

428
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:54,548
ROSE: Oh, my God!

429
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,550
-What the hell have you done?
-It wasn't me.

430
00:27:56,633 --> 00:27:58,343
One touch
and you get every disease in the world.

431
00:27:58,427 --> 00:28:00,971
And I want that body safe, Cassandra.
We've got to go down.

432
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,223
But there's thousands of them.

433
00:28:03,765 --> 00:28:05,601
DOCTOR: Down, down, go down!

434
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:10,564
Quarantine the building!

435
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:12,900
(PA) This building is under quarantine.

436
00:28:15,444 --> 00:28:18,655
Repeat, this building is under quarantine.

437
00:28:19,615 --> 00:28:21,700
No one may leave the premises.

438
00:28:21,783 --> 00:28:25,537
Repeat, no one may leave the premises.

439
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:31,376
DOCTOR: Keep going! Go down!

440
00:28:36,006 --> 00:28:38,342
(WHISPERING) Help us. Save us.

441
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:40,969
(SCREAMING) Help me!

442
00:28:57,194 --> 00:29:00,614
No, the lifts have closed down.
There's a quarantine, nothing's moving.

443
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,199
This way!

444
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:08,997
Don't let them touch you!

445
00:29:09,081 --> 00:29:11,917
Leave him! This is a clone thing.
He's only got a half-life. Come on!

446
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,920
-Mistress!
-I'm sorry, I can't let her escape.

447
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:16,672
My mistress!

448
00:29:26,348 --> 00:29:28,850
Excuse me, can we get some service?

449
00:29:34,398 --> 00:29:36,066
(SCREAMING)

450
00:29:47,202 --> 00:29:49,705
We're trapped! What are we going to do?

451
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:52,541
Well, for starters,
you're going to leave that body.

452
00:29:52,624 --> 00:29:55,377
That psycho-graft is banned
on every civilised planet.

453
00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:57,421
You're compressing Rose to death.

454
00:29:57,546 --> 00:29:59,631
But I've got nowhere to go.

455
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:01,967
My original skin's dead.

456
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:06,054
Not my problem. You can float
as atoms in the air. Now get out.

457
00:30:08,515 --> 00:30:09,975
Give her back to me.

458
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:11,685
You asked for it.

459
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:20,652
Blimey, my head.

460
00:30:22,654 --> 00:30:23,905
Where did she go?

461
00:30:23,989 --> 00:30:27,993
Oh my, this is...different.

462
00:30:28,285 --> 00:30:30,912
-Cassandra?
-Goodness me, I'm a man.

463
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:35,250
Yum. So many parts. And hardly used.

464
00:30:36,585 --> 00:30:39,087
Oh! Ah! Two hearts!

465
00:30:39,755 --> 00:30:41,840
Oh, baby, I'm beating out a samba.

466
00:30:41,923 --> 00:30:45,052
-Get out of him!
-Ooh, he's slim.

467
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:47,220
And a little bit foxy.

468
00:30:47,304 --> 00:30:51,141
You thought so, too.
I've been inside your head.

469
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:53,435
You've been looking.

470
00:30:54,478 --> 00:30:56,104
You like it.

471
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:01,610
What do we do? What would he do?
The Doctor! What the hell would he do?

472
00:31:01,735 --> 00:31:03,362
Ladder. We've got to get up.

473
00:31:03,445 --> 00:31:05,238
Out of the way, blondie!

474
00:31:05,947 --> 00:31:10,327
Please! Help us!

475
00:31:35,644 --> 00:31:38,397
If you get out of the Doctor's body,
he can think of something.

476
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,856
(MIMICKING ROSE)

477
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:43,610
God, it was tedious inside your head.
Hormone city.

478
00:31:43,693 --> 00:31:46,154
But we're gonna die if... Ow!

479
00:31:47,114 --> 00:31:48,198
Get off!

480
00:31:48,323 --> 00:31:51,076
All our good work. All that healing.

481
00:31:51,159 --> 00:31:55,914
The good name of the Sisterhood.
You have destroyed everything!

482
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:59,835
-Go and play with a ball of string.
-Everywhere, disease.

483
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:02,796
This is the human world. Sickness!

484
00:32:03,547 --> 00:32:05,215
(SCREAMING)

485
00:32:15,809 --> 00:32:17,102
Move!

486
00:32:18,311 --> 00:32:21,606
(PA) Maximum quarantine.
Divert all shuttles.

487
00:32:23,567 --> 00:32:25,068
Help us.

488
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:28,780
-Now what do we do?
-Use the sonic screwdriver.

489
00:32:28,864 --> 00:32:31,408
-You mean this thing?
-Yes, I mean that thing!

490
00:32:31,533 --> 00:32:34,161
But I don't know how!
That Doctor's hidden away all his thoughts.

491
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,830
Cassandra, go back into me.
The Doctor can open it.

492
00:32:36,913 --> 00:32:38,081
Do it!

493
00:32:38,206 --> 00:32:39,624
Hold on tight.

494
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:47,716
Oh, chav-tastic again.

495
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,718
-Open it!
-Not till you get out of her!

496
00:32:49,801 --> 00:32:53,054
-We need the Doctor.
-I order you to leave her!

497
00:32:56,558 --> 00:33:00,228
No matter how difficult the situation,
there is no need to shout.

498
00:33:00,395 --> 00:33:01,980
Cassandra, get out of him!

499
00:33:02,063 --> 00:33:04,399
But if I go into you, he simply refuses.
He's so rude.

500
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:06,776
I don't care, just do something!

501
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:09,529
Oh, I'm so going to regret this.

502
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:17,913
Oh, sweet Lord! I look disgusting.

503
00:33:19,372 --> 00:33:21,583
-Nice to have you back.
-No, you don't.

504
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:27,464
That is your last warning, Cassandra.

505
00:33:27,756 --> 00:33:29,591
Inside her head...

506
00:33:31,593 --> 00:33:33,470
They're so alone.

507
00:33:33,595 --> 00:33:36,056
They keep reaching out, just to hold us.

508
00:33:38,308 --> 00:33:42,437
All their lives
and they've never been touched.

509
00:33:53,782 --> 00:33:55,325
(BANGING)

510
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:07,003
We're safe, we're safe, we're safe!
We're clean, we're clean! Look, look.

511
00:34:07,087 --> 00:34:09,548
-Show me your skin.
-Look! Clean! Look!

512
00:34:09,631 --> 00:34:11,967
If we'd been touched, we'd be dead.

513
00:34:13,385 --> 00:34:15,303
How's it going up here? What's the status?

514
00:34:15,428 --> 00:34:18,515
Nothing but silence from the other wards.
I think we're the only ones left.

515
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:20,559
I've been trying to override the quarantine.

516
00:34:20,642 --> 00:34:24,229
If I can trip a signal over to New New York,
they can send a private executive squad.

517
00:34:24,312 --> 00:34:26,982
You can't do that. If they forced entry,
they'd break quarantine.

518
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:28,608
I am not dying in here.

519
00:34:28,692 --> 00:34:30,735
We can't let
a single particle of disease get out.

520
00:34:30,819 --> 00:34:34,364
There's 10 million people in that city,
they'd all be at risk. Now turn that off.

521
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:35,907
Not if it gets me out.

522
00:34:35,991 --> 00:34:39,744
All right, fine.
So I have to stop you lot as well. Suits me.

523
00:34:39,828 --> 00:34:42,998
Rose, Novice Hame, everyone!
Excuse me, Your Grace.

524
00:34:43,081 --> 00:34:46,668
Get me the intravenous solutions
for every single disease! Move it!

525
00:35:01,391 --> 00:35:04,811
-How's that? Will that do?
-I don't know. Will it do for what?

526
00:35:04,894 --> 00:35:06,855
The lifts aren't working...

527
00:35:07,689 --> 00:35:09,316
Not moving, different thing.

528
00:35:11,067 --> 00:35:12,277
Here we go.

529
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:14,112
But you're not going to...

530
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:17,490
What do you think you're doing?

531
00:35:17,574 --> 00:35:19,159
(MUMBLING)

532
00:35:22,579 --> 00:35:23,872
Come on.

533
00:35:24,039 --> 00:35:25,832
Not in a million years.

534
00:35:25,915 --> 00:35:29,628
I need another pair of hands.
What do you think?

535
00:35:29,711 --> 00:35:33,048
If you're so desperate to stay alive,
why don't you live a little?

536
00:35:34,257 --> 00:35:36,009
Seal the door!

537
00:35:36,343 --> 00:35:37,844
(MOANING) Help.

538
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:39,387
No!

539
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:45,435
You're completely mad.
I can see why she likes you.

540
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,062
Going down!

541
00:36:01,201 --> 00:36:02,911
Well, that's one way to lose weight.

542
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:05,080
Now, listen.
When I say so, take hold of that lever.

543
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:07,040
There's still a quarantine down there.
We can't...

544
00:36:07,123 --> 00:36:08,792
Hold that lever!

545
00:36:08,917 --> 00:36:12,504
I'm cooking up a cocktail.
I know a bit about medicine myself.

546
00:36:22,222 --> 00:36:25,016
Now, that lever's gonna resist,
but keep it in position.

547
00:36:26,059 --> 00:36:29,062
-Hold on to it with everything you've got.
-What about you?

548
00:36:29,145 --> 00:36:30,772
I've got an appointment. The Doctor is in.

549
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:40,115
I'm in here! Come on!

550
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:41,574
Don't tell them!

551
00:36:41,658 --> 00:36:43,118
Pull that lever!

552
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:47,914
DOCTOR: Come and get me! Come on.
I'm in here! Come on!

553
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:53,044
-(PA) Commence stage one disinfection.
-Come and get me. Come on!

554
00:36:56,297 --> 00:36:57,841
Come on. Come on.

555
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:06,224
All they want to do is pass it on.

556
00:37:06,307 --> 00:37:07,726
Pass it on!

557
00:37:07,851 --> 00:37:09,144
Pass on what?

558
00:37:09,352 --> 00:37:11,104
Pass on what?

559
00:37:11,187 --> 00:37:12,564
Pass it on!

560
00:37:18,528 --> 00:37:21,364
(HISSING)

561
00:37:50,435 --> 00:37:54,439
What did they pass on? Did you kill them?
All of them?

562
00:37:54,522 --> 00:37:57,942
No, that's your way of doing things.

563
00:38:00,695 --> 00:38:03,239
I'm the Doctor and I cured them.

564
00:38:07,535 --> 00:38:11,790
That's right. Hey! There we go, sweetheart.

565
00:38:11,873 --> 00:38:13,416
Hey?

566
00:38:13,917 --> 00:38:17,295
Go to him. Go. That's it. That's it.

567
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:22,967
It's a new subspecies, Cassandra.
A brand-new form of life.

568
00:38:23,551 --> 00:38:26,095
New humans. Look at them! Look!

569
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:31,100
Run by cats, kept in the dark, fed by tubes,

570
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:34,521
but completely, completely alive!

571
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:37,732
You can't deny them
'cause you helped create them.

572
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:41,069
The human race just keeps on going.

573
00:38:41,194 --> 00:38:44,239
Keeps on changing. Life will out.

574
00:38:45,031 --> 00:38:46,282
Ha!

575
00:38:46,908 --> 00:38:50,537
MAN: This is the NNYPD.
Please step away from the shuttles.

576
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:54,666
(PA) All staff will present themselves
to the officers for immediate arrest.

577
00:38:54,749 --> 00:38:57,502
I repeat. Immediate arrest.

578
00:38:57,585 --> 00:39:01,256
All new life forms will be catalogued
and taken into care.

579
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:05,510
All visitors to the hospital will be
required to make a statement

580
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:07,929
to the NNYPD.

581
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:09,764
The Face of Boe!

582
00:39:20,942 --> 00:39:22,569
You were supposed to be dying.

583
00:39:22,694 --> 00:39:26,406
There are better things to do today.
Dying can wait.

584
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:28,575
Oh, I hate telepathy.

585
00:39:29,117 --> 00:39:31,035
Just what I need, a head full of big-face.

586
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:32,287
Shh!

587
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:34,664
I had grown tired with the universe, Doctor,

588
00:39:34,747 --> 00:39:37,876
but you have taught me to look at it anew.

589
00:39:37,959 --> 00:39:40,712
There are legends, you know,

590
00:39:40,795 --> 00:39:42,964
saying that you're millions of years old.

591
00:39:43,089 --> 00:39:45,174
Well, now, that would be impossible.

592
00:39:45,258 --> 00:39:46,843
DOCTOR: Wouldn't it just?

593
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:50,555
I got the impression there was
something you wanted to tell me.

594
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:52,098
A great secret.

595
00:39:52,181 --> 00:39:54,142
So the legend says.

596
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,476
It can wait.

597
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,270
Oh, does it have to?

598
00:39:57,395 --> 00:40:02,066
We shall meet again, Doctor,
for the third time, for the last time,

599
00:40:02,191 --> 00:40:03,860
and the truth shall be told.

600
00:40:04,903 --> 00:40:06,362
Until that day...

601
00:40:11,951 --> 00:40:13,620
That is enigmatic.

602
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:16,205
That is...that is textbook enigmatic.

603
00:40:19,709 --> 00:40:21,461
And now for you.

604
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:28,343
But everything's happy.
Everything's fine. Can't you just leave me?

605
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:29,844
You've lived long enough.

606
00:40:31,012 --> 00:40:33,973
Leave that body and end it, Cassandra.

607
00:40:35,516 --> 00:40:37,310
I don't want to die.

608
00:40:37,393 --> 00:40:38,603
No one does.

609
00:40:38,686 --> 00:40:40,772
-Help me.
-I can't.

610
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:42,357
Mistress...

611
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,150
Oh! You're alive!

612
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:47,528
I kept myself safe for you, mistress.

613
00:40:48,196 --> 00:40:49,614
A body!

614
00:40:50,698 --> 00:40:53,117
And not just that. A volunteer!

615
00:40:53,201 --> 00:40:55,078
Don't you dare! He's got a life of his own.

616
00:40:55,161 --> 00:40:57,413
But I worship the mistress.

617
00:40:57,538 --> 00:40:58,873
I welcome her.

618
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:00,833
You can't, Cassandra. You...

619
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:04,545
Oh! You all right?

620
00:41:07,590 --> 00:41:08,758
Okay?

621
00:41:10,802 --> 00:41:12,053
Yeah.

622
00:41:13,262 --> 00:41:14,305
Hello.

623
00:41:14,389 --> 00:41:16,391
Hello. Welcome back.

624
00:41:16,474 --> 00:41:19,394
Oh, sweet Lord! I'm a walking doodle.

625
00:41:19,686 --> 00:41:22,981
You can't stay in there.
I'm sorry, Cassandra, but that's not fair.

626
00:41:23,064 --> 00:41:25,233
I can take you to the city.
They can build you a skin-tank,

627
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:27,485
and you can stand trial
for what you've done.

628
00:41:27,568 --> 00:41:29,988
Well, that would be rather dramatic.

629
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:33,199
Possibly my finest hour,
and certainly my finest hat.

630
00:41:33,282 --> 00:41:35,034
But I'm afraid we don't have time.

631
00:41:35,118 --> 00:41:37,036
Poor little Chip, he's only a half-life.

632
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:40,540
And he's been through so much.
His heart is racing so.

633
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,794
He's failing.
I don't think he's going to last...

634
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:47,255
-You all right?
-I'm fine.

635
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:53,177
I'm dying.

636
00:41:54,429 --> 00:41:55,972
But that's fine.

637
00:41:57,682 --> 00:41:59,350
I can take you to the city.

638
00:41:59,475 --> 00:42:00,768
No, you won't.

639
00:42:01,602 --> 00:42:03,604
Everything's new on this planet.

640
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:06,357
There's no place for Chip and me anymore.

641
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:11,404
You were right, Doctor.

642
00:42:11,487 --> 00:42:12,864
It's time to die.

643
00:42:17,285 --> 00:42:19,078
And that's good.

644
00:42:21,372 --> 00:42:24,125
Come on, there's one last thing I can do.

645
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:28,921
(WHOOSHING)

646
00:42:31,007 --> 00:42:32,884
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

647
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:41,309
CASSANDRA: Oh, no don't!

648
00:42:43,144 --> 00:42:45,480
That's simply not true.

649
00:42:45,605 --> 00:42:48,066
And believe me, it was so dismal.

650
00:42:48,149 --> 00:42:50,193
And the mosquitoes, I can't tell you.
They were...

651
00:42:50,276 --> 00:42:52,070
Thank you.

652
00:42:52,153 --> 00:42:55,031
Just go. And don't look back.

653
00:42:56,115 --> 00:42:57,658
Good luck.

654
00:43:07,585 --> 00:43:12,048
And if you actually see them, you're shot!
But don't quote me on that.

655
00:43:14,092 --> 00:43:17,095
-A bientot.
-Excuse me, the Lady Cassandra?

656
00:43:17,178 --> 00:43:19,764
I'm sorry, I don't need anything right now.
I'm fine, thank you.

657
00:43:19,847 --> 00:43:23,017
No, I just wanted to say...
you look beautiful.

658
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:29,232
Well. That's very kind,
you strange little thing.

659
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:31,317
Thank you very much.

660
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:32,819
I mean it.

661
00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:39,075
You look...

662
00:43:40,368 --> 00:43:41,869
so beautiful.

663
00:43:47,041 --> 00:43:48,209
Thank you.

664
00:43:52,213 --> 00:43:56,050
Oh, my Lord. Are you all right?
What is it? What's wrong?

665
00:43:56,134 --> 00:43:57,885
Someone get some help!

666
00:43:58,010 --> 00:44:00,471
Call a medic or something, quickly.

667
00:44:00,555 --> 00:44:02,890
I don't know, he just came up to me.

668
00:44:03,015 --> 00:44:04,475
Don't even know his name.

669
00:44:04,559 --> 00:44:09,188
He just collapsed.
I think he's dying. Someone do something!

670
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:13,568
I've got you, sweetheart. It's all right.
There you are.

671
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:16,070
There you are. I've got you.

672
00:44:16,195 --> 00:44:18,990
It'll be alright. There, there.

673
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:20,741
You poor little thing.

674
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:36,841
Might I introduce
Her Majesty Queen Victoria?

675
00:44:43,890 --> 00:44:46,434
MAN: Every full moon,
the howling rings through the valley.

676
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:48,936
This is a man who becomes an animal.

677
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:50,188
A werewolf?

678
00:44:50,271 --> 00:44:52,273
WOMAN: But it can't be an actual wolf.

679
00:44:52,356 --> 00:44:53,608
(GROWLING)

680
00:45:00,990 --> 00:45:02,366
Bullets can't stop it!

681
00:45:02,950 --> 00:45:04,368
(HOWLING)

